<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="T" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Turkish" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Turkish,</orth> pertaining to the Turks: <cit><quote>covered o'er with T. tapestry,</quote> <bibl n="shak. err 4.1.104" default="NO" valid="yes">Err. IV, 1, 104</bibl></cit> (cf. <bibl n="shak. shr 2.355" default="NO" valid="yes">Shr. II, 355</bibl>). <cit><quote>this is the English, not the T. court,</quote> <bibl n="shak. 2h4 5.2.47" default="NO" valid="yes">H4B V, 2, 47</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>like T. mute,</quote> <bibl n="shak. h5 1.2.232" default="NO" valid="yes">H5 I, 2, 232</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>a T. fleet,</quote> <bibl n="shak. oth 1.3.8" default="NO" valid="yes">Oth. I, 3, 8</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. oth 1.3.8" default="NO" valid="yes">Oth. I, 3, 8</bibl> <bibl n="shak. oth 2.1.10" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 1, 10</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. oth 2.1.10" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 1, 10</bibl> <bibl n="shak. oth 2.1.10" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 1, 10</bibl> <bibl n="shak. oth 2.2.4" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 2, 4</bibl>.
